SESSION LOG
===========
Timestamp : 20260408_084402
User      : Alfred
Request   : What would you like me to plan? I want to create 2  mini tools that mirror actual tools I have. Each tool is around 10 cm long. I also want to create and a box to store them.

APPROVED PLAN
-------------
Step 1: Fusion 360
Design the two 10 cm mini tools and the custom storage box to hold them. Create detailed 3D models for each.
Duration: 5h - Booking required: No

Step 2: PreForm
Prepare the 3D models of the two mini tools for SLA 3D printing. This includes orienting the parts, adding necessary support structures, and setting print parameters.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No

Step 3: SLA 3D Printer
Print the two mini tools. The SLA process will ensure high detail and a smooth surface finish, mimicking actual tools.
Duration: 6h - Booking required: Yes

Step 4: UV Curing Station
Post-cure the SLA printed mini tools to achieve optimal material properties and strength.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: Yes

Step 5: Cura
Prepare the 3D model of the storage box for FDM 3D printing. This involves orienting the part, adding supports if necessary, and slicing the model into layers for the printer.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No

Step 6: FDM 3D Printer
Print the custom storage box using FDM technology. This method is suitable for a functional container.
Duration: 8h - Booking required: Yes

Step 7: Support Removal Tools
Carefully remove all support structures from both the SLA printed mini tools and the FDM printed storage box.
Duration: 2h - Booking required: No

Step 8: Sanding & Polishing Tools
Sand and polish the surfaces of the mini tools and the storage box to achieve a smooth finish and refined appearance.
Duration: 3h - Booking required: No

Step 9: Calipers
Perform a final quality check by measuring the dimensions of the mini tools and the storage box to ensure they match the design specifications.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No

Step 10: Paints and Coating
Apply paints or coatings to the mini tools and/or the storage box to enhance their aesthetics and mirror the look of actual tools.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No


